&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;double-checked-initialization-with-synchronized-block-and-volatile-variable&#34;&gt;Double-checked initialization with synchronized block and volatile variable
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this approach, similar the previous one, the synchronization overhead is reduced by synchronizing only the first time the instance is accessed.
The instance variable is marked as &lt;code&gt;volatile&lt;/code&gt; to prevent the occurrence of partially constructed instances.&lt;/p&gt;
